## Phase 3 – Trajectory & Impact Layer

### Objectives
1. Build the Developmental Trajectory Engine to compute longitudinal developmental coefficients per child.
2. Implement risk transition logic (e.g., Low→High between screening intervals).
3. Implement cohort-level impact metrics for block/district/state aggregation.
4. Expose trajectory data through the API for dashboard consumption.

### Deliverables
- D3.1 Trajectory Engine service (Python microservice or integrated FastAPI module)
- D3.2 TimescaleDB hypertable schema and partitioning configuration
- D3.3 Developmental coefficient calculation methodology document
- D3.4 Risk transition event table and alerting triggers
- D3.5 Cohort aggregation batch job (Celery + SQL)
- D3.6 Trajectory API endpoints (documented with OpenAPI spec)

### Technical Stack
- Python 3.11+, FastAPI, TimescaleDB 2.x, SQLAlchemy (async), Celery, Redis
- Pandas, NumPy for coefficient computation
- Alembic for schema migrations
- Pytest for service-level unit and integration tests

### Risks
| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| Sparse longitudinal data (children screened only once) | High | Medium | Trajectory engine handles single time-point gracefully; flags as insufficient for trajectory |
| TimescaleDB performance under high write volume | Low | Medium | Tune chunk intervals; implement write buffer via async queue |
| Coefficient definition contested by domain experts | Medium | Medium | Define coefficient as standardised score relative to age-cohort; pre-agree with domain partners |

### Validation Criteria
- Trajectory computed correctly for simulated 12-month longitudinal cohort (500 children)
- Risk transition events detected accurately (unit tested with known before/after scenarios)
- Cohort aggregation query completes in ≤ 5 seconds for district-scale 10,000-child dataset
- API endpoints return correct trajectory data; documented in OpenAPI spec

### Exit Checklist
- [ ] Trajectory Engine service passes all unit and integration tests
- [ ] Coefficient methodology approved by domain expert
- [ ] Risk transition events correctly logged and queryable
- [ ] Cohort batch job completes within SLA on load test dataset
- [ ] OpenAPI spec generated and committed to repository

---

## Phase 4 – Dashboard Layer

### Objectives
1. Build role-specific dashboards: AWW (Android embedded), Supervisor (web), CDPO (web), State (web), Audit Log Console.
2. Implement RBAC-enforced data scoping (AWW sees own anganwadi only; Supervisor sees block; etc.).
3. Implement referral action workflow for AWW (mark child for referral, record follow-up).
4. Implement alert/notification system for new High/Critical risk flags.

### Deliverables
- D4.1 AWW dashboard embedded in Android App (child list, risk flags, referral screen)
- D4.2 Supervisor web dashboard (React)
- D4.3 CDPO web dashboard (React)
- D4.4 State analytics dashboard (React + Metabase/Apache Superset integration)
- D4.5 Audit Log Console (React admin panel)
- D4.6 Notification service (FCM for Android push; email digest for web users)
- D4.7 UI/UX accessibility audit report (WCAG 2.1 AA compliance)

### Technical Stack
- React 18+ (TypeScript), TailwindCSS, Recharts/Nivo for charts
- Kotlin (Android) for AWW embedded dashboard
- FastAPI for dashboard API endpoints
- Apache Superset or Metabase (open-source, on-prem) for state-level BI
- Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) for Android push notifications (or on-prem alternative via APNS/FCM-parity server)

### Risks
| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|---|
| AWW literacy levels make complex UI unusable | High | High | Conduct HCD (Human-Centred Design) sessions with AWWs; use icon-driven UI, minimal text |
| State dashboard too complex for CDPO adoption | Medium | Medium | Provide default views with export-to-Excel; minimise configuration burden |
| FCM dependency on Google services | Low | Medium | Evaluate on-prem push alternative (ntfy, Unified Push) for air-gapped environments |
| Accessibility standards not met | Medium | Low | Include accessibility audit in Phase 6; fix before Phase 7 pilot |

### Validation Criteria
- All dashboards pass RBAC tests (cross-role data isolation confirmed)
- AWW dashboard usability tested with ≥ 5 real AWWs and System Usability Scale (SUS) score ≥ 70
- Supervisor/CDPO dashboards load within 3 seconds at P95 for district-scale data
- Notification delivery tested end-to-end (FCM to device)

### Exit Checklist
- [ ] RBAC data scoping verified for all 5 dashboard roles
- [ ] AWW dashboard SUS score ≥ 70 in usability test
- [ ] All API endpoints backing dashboards load within 3s SLA
- [ ] Audit Log Console displays and exports correctly
- [ ] Notification system tested end-to-end

